"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-07-paris-2024-olympics-amusan-breezes-into-womens-100m-hurdles-semis\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Tobi Amusan is through to the semi-finals of women's 100m hurdles at the 2024 Olympic Games.  The world record holder won her heat in a time of 12.49s.  Alaysha Johnson was second in a time of 12.61s, while Janeek Brown came third in 12.84s.  Amusan is one of the favourites to win gold medal in the event.  The 27-year-old finished fourth in the women's 100m hurdles three years ago in Tokyo.  The semi-final will hold at the Stade de France on Thursday.  LaLiga: Ancelotti picks player that will replace Kroos at Real Madrid  EPL: Maresca blames Pochettino for one 'habit' among Chelsea players  2025 World Championships: Amusan credits 'God' for silver medal success  Amusan confirms for Diamond League season opener  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"